Title:
This is the second time flying on this airline and unfortunately it's the recommendation of both travel agents used...
The fact that one travels business class means that there are certain expectations which come with the purchase of this class ticket...
Notwithstanding the fact that these were both old airplanes to and fro with old fashioned business class seats...
- First and foremost is the check in process... upon arrival at the airport we found that economy class check in was open whilst business had nobody available to assist with the process;
- Second smack in your face is the fact that normally business class is priority pass or separate queuing when it's boarding time... this certainly does not occur with this airline in no shape or form from Cape Town International airport departure area;
- Food is mediocre and does not even reach economy class standards on other airlines long haul. The menu is beautiful, reads and sounds delicious but reality was bland tasting, tough pastries, wilted vegetable and the list continues;
- Staff are disdainful and it feels as if they are doing you a favour...
- Another case in point was the children from economy class and their parents kept on coming and playing right next to our seat... we have nothing against little babies or children however we did purchase our tickets for a certain reason and the attendants didn't address the issue at all;
- Upon arrival normally business class luggage arrives first, mine was the last to arrive off the conveyor system;
- Similar issues occurred upon the return trip with a major case in point being that the airline apparently had a policy that it's ok for other clients to spray a horrible tea tree oil substance continuously in the small enclosed space and couldn't ask the passengers in question to refrain from such an activity as the other passengers were all gagging... I personally had to lie flat down nauseous for virtually the entire flight as the smell was so pungent. My partner on the other hand had to walk through to the back of the plane to try and catch his breath.

Mauritius is a vacation destination and for us our holiday begins from the airport and not once we land on the other side... this is state of mind when one is traveling for sheer pleasure...

Sad state of airline...
